We need to change the shape of the WAR distribution, delete entityengine.xml and modify the ant script. Possibly removing the edit tree.

The past method of WAR distribution WAR file creation is to use an ant build script which merges changes in an edit tree with the original exploded WAR tree.

The edit tree contains an entityengine.xml file which users are instructed to modify for their db configuration. The docs must change but the entityengine.xml file should now not be there. This means the edit tree is probably pointless now since there is no expected set of edits required. The WAR file can just be booted as is unless there are non-standard edits required.

